 very fast solar wind streams (~1000 km/s)\nand intense fluxes of solar energetic particles. We speculated that anomalous\ndynamics of the magnetosphere could be well described by the models if the He\nabundance in the solar wind was assumed to be >20%, which is well appropriate\nfor erupting filaments and which is in agreement with the upper 27% threshold\nfor the He/H ratio obtained from Cluster measurements.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Feb 2014 03:33:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-02-06"}
